line_1: Till where dark wood the hills slope surface shrouds;
line_2: Or the blue summit mingles with the clouds;

line_1: And night's thick veil the guilty mourner shrouds.
line_2: To pierce the heavy and umbrageous clouds;

line_1: Piercing, with uprais'd eyes, each mist that shrouds,
line_2: By airs etherial wafted from the clouds:
Aspire to pierce the vagrant clouds!

line_1: Command your slain, ye heroes, from their shrouds;
line_2: Bring, ye bright fair, your love-attending crouds;
Its lofty head among surrounding clouds:

line_1: While thus they pass, the Sun his Glory shrouds,
line_2: The changing Skies hang out their sable Clouds;

line_1: Where, nursed in night, incumbent Tempest shrouds
line_2: The seeds of Thunder in circumfluent clouds,

line_1: Curtain'd with night the couch imperial shrouds,
line_2: And rests the crimson cushions upon clouds. —

line_1: From mortal ken himself the Almighty shrouds
line_2: Pavilion'd in thick night and circumambient clouds.

line_1: All slow, and wan, and wrap'd with Shrouds,

line_2: By me pass the ghastly crowds,
